    "name": "Artificer Materials",
    "type": "Crafting",
    "subType": "Materials",
    "description": "The base material for crafting items with Artificing is Iron Artifice parts.  You can either buy Iron Artifice parts or convert them from Iron by using the Artificer or Transmuter abilities. Artifice weapons follow special rules. Weapon attachments follow the regular artifice rules however. Iron: Equal artifice parts to the base clim cost of the artifice is required to craft Iron Artifices. Outside of iron, there are a variety of special materials that an Artificer can use while crafting. These are more expensive, but grant additional C mod slots to the artifice. You need Artifice Parts of the matching type to craft and the amount you need is determined this way: (Special Material Modifier) x (Base Clim Cost) = Amount of Special Material Artifice Parts Needed Iron Artifice Parts Multiplier: 1x Effect: 1 C mod slot Tamahagane Artifice Parts Multiplier: 1x Effect: 2 C mod slots Mithril Artifice Parts Multiplier: 2x Effect: 3 C mod slots Orichalcum Artifice Parts Multiplier: 2x Effect: 4 C mod slots Escudo Artifice Parts Multiplier 3x Effect: 5 C mod slots Artificing Weapon Materials: The base material for crafting weapons such as pistols or sniper rifles with artificing is Iron. Iron units must be converted into an ingot before they can be used. Iron: Clim Cost per ingot: 300 Clim Unit cost per ingot: 500 Iron units Effect: None When using Iron to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot. Outside of iron, there are a variety of special materials that an artificer can use while crafting. These are more expensive, but grant stat bonuses. NOTE: When making an Artifice weapon that is an actual weapon and not an attachment, you must spend an additional iron artifice parts equal to the cost of the weapon - 500 rather than an extra ingot. This also applies to guns. Tamahagane Clim Cost per ingot: 1050 Clim Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Tamahagane units. Effect: +1 stat bonus When using Tamahagane to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Tamahagane. Mithril Clim Cost per ingot: 4050 Clim Unit cost per ingot: 8000 Mithril units. Effect: +1/+1 stat bonus When using Mithril to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Mithril. Orichalcum Clim Cost per ingot: 8050 Clim Unit cost per ingot: 16000 Orihalcum units. Effect: +2/+1 stat bonus When using Orihalcum to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Orihalcum. Escudo Clim Cost per ingot: 11550 Clim Unit cost per ingot: 23000 Escudo units. Effect: +2/+2 stat bonus When using Escudo to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Escudo. Stat bonuses depend on if the crafted item is a tool or weapon. Weapon : The Material bonuses to go Focus and Power. With getting a +1 bonus or a +2/+1 bonus, the crafter may choose which of the two stats gets the extra bonus. Artificing special materials Dark Iron (550 Clim / 15 Crafting Points) : Unit cost per ingot:  1000 Dark Iron units. Strikes with Dark Iron infused weapons cause the target to be unable to teleport until the end of their next turn. Silver (1050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Silver units. Dealing damage with Silver infused weapons disables the Regeneration effect of Fiends until the start of your next turn. Electrum (3050 Clim/ 30 Crafting Points): Unit cost per ingot: 6000 Electrum units. Strikes with Electrum infused weapons grant a +2 Electrum Power bonus against Divines, Summons or Otherworlders. Mycelite (1550 Clim / 20 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Mycelite units. Mycelite infused weapons incur 1 less burden to a minimum of 1 Obsidian Steel (550 Clim) Unit cost per ingot:  1000 Obsidian Steel units. Obsidian Steel infused weapons cannot be the targets of magical effects. Adamantite (2050 Clim / 20 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 4000 Adamantite units Adamantite weapons cannot be destroyed by non adamantite tools or weapons. Luxaeterna (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Luxaeterna units. Changes the physical damage type into Holy. Corvuskite (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Corvuskite units. Changes the physical damage type into Dark. Arcanium (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Arcanium units. Changes the physical damage type into Arcane. Fulgarite ( 1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points ) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Fulgarite units Changes the physical damage type into Lightning. Vivinthal (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Vivinthal units. Changes the physical damage type into Water. Glacite (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Glacite units. Changes the physical damage type into Frost. Salachar (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Salachar units. Changes the physical damage type into Fire. Sylphsteel (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Sylphsteel units Changes the physical damage type into Wind. Ghimslag (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Ghimslag units. Changes the physical damage type into Earth. Nullite ( 2050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): Unit cost per ingot: 4000 Nullite units All attacks made with this weapon gain the Shieldbreaker property. Runesteel ( 1050 Clim / 10 Crafting Points): Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Runesteel units This weapon can channel spells as if it was a channeling weapon. Sepsium ( 2050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): Unit cost per ingot: 4000 Sepsium units When damaging a creature with this weapon, they cannot recover HP (except for regeneration type effects) until the start of your next turn. Sunsteel ( 1550 Clim / 15 Crafting Points): Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Sunsteel units Attacks with this weapon gain Full Pierce against creatures weak to light or sunlight.",
