    "type": "Crafting",
    "subType": "Materials",
    "description": "Blacksmithing Base Materials The base material for crafting items with blacksmithing is Iron. Iron units must be converted into an ingot before they can be used. Iron: Clim Cost per ingot: 300 Clim Unit cost per ingot: 500 Iron units Effect: None When using Iron to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot for a one handed weapon or tool, or 2 for a longsword or two handed weapon (or two handed tool). Outside of iron, there are a variety of special materials that a blacksmith can use while crafting. These are more expensive, but grant stat bonuses Tamahagane Clim Cost per ingot: 1050 Clim Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Tamahagane units. Effect: +1 stat bonus When using Tamahagane to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Tamahagane. If making a two handed weapon, you must add an additional ingot of Iron. Mithril Clim Cost per ingot: 4050 Clim Unit cost per ingot: 8000 Mithril units. Effect: +1/+1 stat bonus When using Mithril to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Mithril. If making a two handed weapon, you must add an additional ingot of Iron. Orichalcum Clim Cost per ingot: 8050 Clim Unit cost per ingot: 16000 Orihalcum units. Effect: +2/+1 stat bonus When using Orihalcum to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Orihalcum. If making a two handed weapon, you must add an additional ingot of Iron. Escudo Clim Cost per ingot: 11550 Clim Unit cost per ingot: 23000 Escudo units. Effect: +2/+2 stat bonus When using Escudo to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Escudo. If making a two handed weapon, you must add an additional ingot of Iron. Stat bonuses depend on if the crafted item is a tool or weapon. Weapon : The Material bonuses to go Focus and Power. With getting a +1 bonus or a +2/+1 bonus, the crafter may choose which of the two stats gets the extra bonus. Tool : For tools, there is a crafting bonus and a finish bonus. A crafting bonus gives you +1 (or +2) Material bonus to each crafting dice roll. The finish bonus gives you a +5 (or +10) Finish bonus once at the end of your craft. Blacksmithing Special Materials When these materials are added to a crafting tool, they give a +1 bonus to crafting checks when working with that material. Dark Iron (550 Clim / 15 Crafting Points) : Unit cost per ingot:  1000 Dark Iron units. Strikes with Dark Iron infused weapons cause the target to be unable to teleport until the end of their next turn. Silver (1050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Silver units. Dealing damage with Silver infused weapons disables the Regeneration effect of Fiends until the start of your next turn. Electrum (3050 Clim/ 30 Crafting Points): Unit cost per ingot: 6000 Electrum units. Strikes with Electrum infused weapons grant a +2 Electrum Power bonus against Divines, Summons or Otherworlders. Mycelite (1550 Clim / 20 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Mycelite units. Mycelite infused weapons incur 1 less burden to a minimum of 1 Obsidian Steel (550 Clim) Unit cost per ingot:  1000 Obsidian Steel units. Obsidian Steel infused weapons cannot be the targets of magical effects. Adamantite (2050 Clim / 20 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 4000 Adamantite units Adamantite weapons cannot be destroyed by non adamantite tools or weapons. Luxaeterna (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Luxaeterna units. Changes the physical damage type into Holy. Corvuskite (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Corvuskite units. Changes the physical damage type into Dark. Arcanium (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Arcanium units. Changes the physical damage type into Arcane. Fulgarite ( 1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points ) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Fulgarite units Changes the physical damage type into Lightning. Vivinthal (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Vivinthal units. Changes the physical damage type into Water. Glacite (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Glacite units. Changes the physical damage type into Frost. Salachar (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Salachar units. Changes the physical damage type into Fire. Sylphsteel (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Sylphsteel units Changes the physical damage type into Wind. Ghimslag (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points) Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Ghimslag units. Changes the physical damage type into Earth. Nullite ( 2050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): Unit cost per ingot: 4000 Nullite units All attacks made with this weapon gain the Shieldbreaker property. Runesteel ( 1050 Clim / 10 Crafting Points): Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Runesteel units This weapon can channel spells as if it was a channeling weapon. Sepsium ( 2050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): Unit cost per ingot: 4000 Sepsium units When damaging a creature with this weapon, they cannot recover HP (except for regeneration type effects) until the start of your next turn. Sunsteel ( 1550 Clim / 15 Crafting Points): Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Sunsteel units Attacks with this weapon gain Full Pierce against creatures weak to light or sunlight.",
