    "description": "A pair of goggles that link themselves to the wielder's eyes. Once put on, they are always active. They allow the wielder to see the fluctuations of mana, letting them see the presence of any magic or mana based abilities including traps or barriers.  They can also automatically detect the presence of any creature that has mana that is not behind total cover. (This does not give you vision to attack them if they would be in things such as glittershards). However, they become unable to detect living creatures without mana in them. Due to the nature of these goggles, they must be carefully removed. Removing them takes a minute. Attempting to do it faster will blind the person wielding them for a minute instead. Mods A mods: Mana Sight (20 points): Looking at a target within 30ft automatically reveals their mana %. B mods: Quick Removal (50 points): Can be removed by spending 3 AP instead of 1 minute. Decipher Magic (80 points): When looking at a magic effect, you may attempt to understand it as if using Decipher Magic. Your bonus for this roll is +15, regardless of your reason or magic skill points.",
